data.description: Village of  Bristol one-owner home on an acre (132.5' x 330') of land with municipal sewer and water.  Alesci-built ranch(1978) has 3 bedrooms, 1.5 baths,large poured concrete  basement and small crawl space (under kitchen).  Main bathroom has dual entry (hallway/bedroom) access, hardwood flooring in all bedrooms, newer furnace, hot water tank(August 2019),concrete patio.  Roof replacement in recent years. Being sold ''as is''  Walking distance to Bristol Elementary School. Conservation club of Kenosha County shooting range is on Hwy AH. See attached map for location of tiny area (triangle)floodplain  at rear SW corner of the property. Bristol's first settler was Rollin Tuttle in April 1830.
